{"title_page": "Yesterday's Hero (John Paul Young song)", "text_new": "{{Infobox song\n| name       = Yesterday's Hero\n| cover      = Yesterday's_Hero_(song)_by_John_Paul_Young.jpg\n| alt        =\n| type       = single\n| artist     = [[John Paul Young]]\n| album      = [[Hero (John Paul Young album)|Hero]]\n| released   = 10 February 1975\n| format     = Vinyl, 7\", Single\n| recorded   = 1974\n| studio     =\n| venue      =\n| genre      = [[pop music|Pop]]\n| length     = 3:43\n| label      = [[Albert Productions]]. [[Ariola]]\n| writer     = [[Harry Vanda]], [[George Young (rock musician)|George Young]]\n| producer   = [[Harry Vanda]], [[George Young (rock musician)|George Young]]\n| prev_title = Show and Tell\n| prev_year  = 1974\n| next_title = [[The Love Game (John Paul Young song)|The Love Game]]\n| next_year  = 1975\n}}\n\n\"'''Yesterday's Hero'''\" is a pop song by [[John Paul Young]]. The song was written by [[George Young (rock musician)|George Young]] and [[Harry Vanda]] and was released in February 1975 as the lead single from Young's debut studio album, ''[[Hero (John Paul Young album)|Hero]]'' (1975).\n\nThe song became a worldwide hit, peaking at No. 8 in Australia, No. 1 in South Africa and No. 41 in the United States.\n\n== Overview ==\n\"Yesterday's Hero\" is a song about the fleeting nature of pop stardom. It drew on Vanda & Young's own experiences as former [[teen idols]].<sup>[[John Paul Young#cite note-McF-1|[1]]][[John Paul Young#cite note-Milesago-2|[2]]][[John Paul Young#cite note-APRA Yesterdays-16|[16]]]</sup>\n\nThe song gave Young his first top ten hit,<sup>[[John Paul Young#cite note-Kent-10|[10]]]</sup> reaching No. 8 on the Australian singles chart<sup>[[John Paul Young#cite note-Kent-10|[10]]]</sup> and staying at No. 1 on the [[Melbourne, Victoria|Melbourne]] charts for six weeks before being replaced by [[Hush (band)|Hush]]'s \"[[Bony Moronie|Boney Maroney]]\". The single sold strongly in the United States, where it reached No. 44 on the [[Cash Box]] Top 100 in February 1976.<sup>[[John Paul Young#cite note-17|[17]]]</sup>\n\nOne of the key factors in the Australian success of \"Yesterday's Hero\" was the film clip made to promote it, which enabled the song to be given heavy exposure on ''[[Countdown (Australian TV series)|Countdown]]'', which had just switched to its new one-hour Sunday evening format, following the official start of [[Colour television|colour TV]] broadcasting on 1 March 1975.<sup>[[John Paul Young#cite note-Milesago-2|[2]]][[John Paul Young#cite note-Jeff-18|[18]]][[John Paul Young#cite note-Dave-19|[19]]]</sup> Young's debut performance on ''Countdown'' had him miming \"Yesterday's Hero\" while dressed in a sailor's suit surrounded on an island stage with a studio audience of screaming teen girls.<sup>[[John Paul Young#cite note-Long-20|[20]]]</sup> He was dragged off the stage three times by audience members and the microphone cord was ripped out but the song continued uninterrupted.<sup>[[John Paul Young#cite note-Long-20|[20]]]</sup> [[ABC Television|ABC TV]] producer, Michael Shrimpton believes his show, ''Countdown'', played a big part in making \"Yesterday's Hero\" and Young a teen pop success.<sup>[[John Paul Young#cite note-Jeff-18|[18]]]</sup>\n\n== Track listing ==\n'''7\"''' (AP-10688) / (Ariola 16631 AT)\n*Side A \"Yesterday's Hero\" - 3:43\n*Side B \"The Next Time\" - 3:30\n\n==Charts==\n===Weekly charts===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n!Chart (1975\u201377)\n!Peak<br />position\n|-\n| Australian [[Kent Music Report]] \n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|8\n|-\n| South Africa <ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rock.co.za/files/springbok_top_20_(Y).html|title=South African Rock Lists Website \u2013 SA Charts 1969\u20131989 Acts (Y)|work=South Africa's Rock Lists|publisher=South African Rock Encyclopedia|accessdate=14 August 2009}}</ref>\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|1\n|-\n|{{singlechart|Sweden|10|artist=John Paul Young|album=Yesterday's Here|refname=|accessdate=15 February 2016}}\n|-\n|-\n| US [[Billboard Hot 100|''Billboard Hot'' 100]]<ref>''Joel Whitburn's Top Pop Singles 1955-1990'' - {{ISBN|0-89820-089-X}}</ref><ref>https://www.discogs.com/John-Young-Yesterdays-Hero-The-Next-Time/release/3558979</ref><ref>[http://www.australianmusicdatabase.com/recordings/yesterday-s-hero-b-w-the-next-time-by-john-paul-young Australian Music Database]</ref>\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|42\n|-\n|}\n\n===Year-end charts===\n{|class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\"\n|-\n!scope=\"col\"| Chart (1975)\n!scope=\"col\"| Position\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"| Australia <ref>{{cite book|title=[[Kent Music Report|Australian Chart Book 1970\u20131992]]|last=Kent|first=David|authorlink=David Kent (historian)|publisher=Australian Chart Book|location=[[St Ives, New South Wales|St Ives, NSW]]|year=1993|isbn=0-646-11917-6}} NOTE: Used for Australian Singles and Albums charting from 1970 until [[Australian Recording Industry Association|ARIA]] created their own [[ARIA Charts|charts]] in mid-1988.</ref>\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| 32\n|-\n|}\n\n==Cover versions==\n* [[Bay City Rollers]] (1976)\n* [[Gene Pitney]] did not cover this song. It's of the same name but was released 10 years earlier.\n* Ignatius Jones (1992)\n* Serbian band [[Laki Pingvini]] covered the song as \"Ne, nisam tvoj heroj\" on album \"Muzika za mlade\" 1984.\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n{{John Paul Young}}\n\n[[Category:1975 singles]]\n[[Category:1975 songs]]\n[[Category:Songs written by Harry Vanda]]\n[[Category:Songs written by George Young (rock musician)]]\n[[Category:Song recordings produced by Harry Vanda]]\n[[Category:Song recordings produced by George Young (rock musician)]]\n[[Category:John Paul Young songs]]\n[[Category:Bay City Rollers songs]]\n[[Category:Paul Nicholas songs]]\n[[Category:Number-one singles in South Africa]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox song\n| name       = Yesterday's Hero\n| cover      = Yesterday's_Hero_(song)_by_John_Paul_Young.jpg\n| alt        =\n| type       = single\n| artist     = [[John Paul Young]]\n| album      = [[Hero (John Paul Young album)|Hero]]\n| released   = 10 February 1975\n| format     = Vinyl, 7\", Single\n| recorded   = 1974\n| studio     =\n| venue      =\n| genre      = [[pop music|Pop]]\n| length     = 3:43\n| label      = [[Albert Productions]]. [[Ariola]]\n| writer     = [[Harry Vanda]], [[George Young (rock musician)|George Young]]\n| producer   = [[Harry Vanda]], [[George Young (rock musician)|George Young]]\n| prev_title = Show and Tell\n| prev_year  = 1974\n| next_title = [[The Love Game (John Paul Young song)|The Love Game]]\n| next_year  = 1975\n}}\n\n\"'''Yesterday's Hero'''\" is a pop song by [[John Paul Young]]. The song was written by [[George Young (rock musician)|George Young]] and [[Harry Vanda]] and was released in February 1975 as the lead single from Young's debut studio album, ''[[Hero (John Paul Young album)|Hero]]'' (1975).\n\nThe song became a worldwide hit, peaking at No. 8 in Australia, No. 1 in South Africa and No. 41 in the United States.\n\n== Overview ==\n\"Yesterday's Hero\" is a song about the fleeting nature of pop stardom. It drew on Vanda & Young's own experiences as former [[teen idols]].<sup>[[John Paul Young#cite note-McF-1|[1]]][[John Paul Young#cite note-Milesago-2|[2]]][[John Paul Young#cite note-APRA Yesterdays-16|[16]]]</sup>\n\nThe song gave Young his first top ten hit,<sup>[[John Paul Young#cite note-Kent-10|[10]]]</sup> reaching No. 8 on the Australian singles chart<sup>[[John Paul Young#cite note-Kent-10|[10]]]</sup> and staying at No. 1 on the [[Melbourne, Victoria|Melbourne]] charts for six weeks before being replaced by [[Hush (band)|Hush]]'s \"[[Bony Moronie|Boney Maroney]]\". The single sold strongly in the United States, where it reached No. 44 on the [[Cash Box]] Top 100 in February 1976.<sup>[[John Paul Young#cite note-17|[17]]]</sup>\n\nOne of the key factors in the Australian success of \"Yesterday's Hero\" was the film clip made to promote it, which enabled the song to be given heavy exposure on ''[[Countdown (Australian TV series)|Countdown]]'', which had just switched to its new one-hour Sunday evening format, following the official start of [[Colour television|colour TV]] broadcasting on 1 March 1975.<sup>[[John Paul Young#cite note-Milesago-2|[2]]][[John Paul Young#cite note-Jeff-18|[18]]][[John Paul Young#cite note-Dave-19|[19]]]</sup> Young's debut performance on ''Countdown'' had him miming \"Yesterday's Hero\" while dressed in a sailor's suit surrounded on an island stage with a studio audience of screaming teen girls.<sup>[[John Paul Young#cite note-Long-20|[20]]]</sup> He was dragged off the stage three times by audience members and the microphone cord was ripped out but the song continued uninterrupted.<sup>[[John Paul Young#cite note-Long-20|[20]]]</sup> [[ABC Television|ABC TV]] producer, Michael Shrimpton believes his show, ''Countdown'', played a big part in making \"Yesterday's Hero\" and Young a teen pop success.<sup>[[John Paul Young#cite note-Jeff-18|[18]]]</sup>\n\n== Track listing ==\n'''7\"''' (AP-10688) / (Ariola 16631 AT)\n*Side A \"Yesterday's Hero\" - 3:43\n*Side B \"The Next Time\" - 3:30\n\n==Charts==\n===Weekly charts===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n!Chart (1975\u201377)\n!Peak<br />position\n|-\n| Australian [[Kent Music Report]] \n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|8\n|-\n| South Africa <ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rock.co.za/files/springbok_top_20_(Y).html|title=South African Rock Lists Website \u2013 SA Charts 1969\u20131989 Acts (Y)|work=South Africa's Rock Lists|publisher=South African Rock Encyclopedia|accessdate=14 August 2009}}</ref>\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|1\n|-\n|{{singlechart|Sweden|10|artist=John Paul Young|album=Yesterday's Here|refname=|accessdate=15 February 2016}}\n|-\n|-\n| US [[Billboard Hot 100|''Billboard Hot'' 100]]<ref>''Joel Whitburn's Top Pop Singles 1955-1990'' - {{ISBN|0-89820-089-X}}</ref><ref>https://www.discogs.com/John-Young-Yesterdays-Hero-The-Next-Time/release/3558979</ref><ref>[http://www.australianmusicdatabase.com/recordings/yesterday-s-hero-b-w-the-next-time-by-john-paul-young Australian Music Database]</ref>\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|42\n|-\n|}\n\n===Year-end charts===\n{|class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\"\n|-\n!scope=\"col\"| Chart (1975)\n!scope=\"col\"| Position\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"| [[Kent Music Report]]<ref>{{cite book|title=[[Kent Music Report|Australian Chart Book 1970\u20131992]]|last=Kent|first=David|authorlink=David Kent (historian)|publisher=Australian Chart Book|location=[[St Ives, New South Wales|St Ives, NSW]]|year=1993|isbn=0-646-11917-6}} NOTE: Used for Australian Singles and Albums charting from 1970 until [[Australian Recording Industry Association|ARIA]] created their own [[ARIA Charts|charts]] in mid-1988.</ref>\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| 32\n|-\n|}\n\n==Cover versions==\n* [[Bay City Rollers]] (1976)\n* [[Gene Pitney]] did not cover this song. It's of the same name but was released 10 years earlier.\n* Ignatius Jones (1992)\n* Serbian band [[Laki Pingvini]] covered the song as \"Ne, nisam tvoj heroj\" on album \"Muzika za mlade\" 1984.\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n{{John Paul Young}}\n\n[[Category:1975 singles]]\n[[Category:1975 songs]]\n[[Category:Songs written by Harry Vanda]]\n[[Category:Songs written by George Young (rock musician)]]\n[[Category:Song recordings produced by Harry Vanda]]\n[[Category:Song recordings produced by George Young (rock musician)]]\n[[Category:John Paul Young songs]]\n[[Category:Bay City Rollers songs]]\n[[Category:Paul Nicholas songs]]\n[[Category:Number-one singles in South Africa]]\n", "name_user": "JGabbard", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eYear-end charts:alt w", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Yesterday%27s_Hero_(John_Paul_Young_song)"}
{"title_page": "Mike Temwanjera", "text_new": "{{short description|Zimbabwean footballer}}\n{{EngvarB|date=May 2013}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=May 2013}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n| name      = Mike Temwanjera \n| image =\n| fullname = <!-- if different -->\n| birth_date = {{birth date and age|1982|5|21|df=y}}\n| birth_place = [[Harare]], Zimbabwe \n| height = {{Height|m=1.87|precision=0}} \n| currentclub =\n| clubnumber = \n| position = [[Forward (association football)|Striker]] \n| youthyears1 = | youthclubs1 = \n| years1 = 2001\u20132003 | clubs1 = [[CAPS United]] | caps1 = ? | goals1 = ? \n| years2 = 2003\u20132006 | clubs2 = [[FK Javor Ivanjica|Javor Ivanjica]] | caps2 = 26  | goals2 = 3\n| years3 = 2006\u20132007 | clubs3 = [[FK Borac \u010ca\u010dak|Borac \u010ca\u010dak]] | caps3 = 16 | goals3 = 3\n| years4 = 2007\u20132014 | clubs4 = [[SC Vaslui|Vaslui]] | caps4 = 174 | goals4 = 39\n| years5 = 2014\u20132015| clubs5 = [[Bangkok United F.C.|Bangkok United]] | caps5 = 14 | goals5 = 7\n| nationalyears1 = 2005 | nationalteam1 = [[Zimbabwe national football team|Zimbabwe]] | nationalcaps1 = 1 | nationalgoals1 = 0\n| pcupdate = {{date|2014-11-2}}\n}}\n\n'''Mike Temwanjera ''' (born 21 May 1982, [[Harare]]) is a former [[Zimbabwe]]an [[Association football|footballer]]. He usually played as a [[Forward (association football)#Centre forward|centre forward]], but also as a [[Forward (football)#Second striker|second striker]]. A member of [[FC Vaslui]] from January 2007 until summer 2014, he was one of the team's longest serving players, second in scoring during Vaslui's spell in Liga I, with 39 goals. He also appeared once for the [[Zimbabwe national football team|Zimbabwe national team]].\n\n== Club career ==\n\n=== CAPS United ===\n\nTemwanjera played until 2003 with [[CAPS United F.C.|CAPS United]], traditionally one of the strongest teams in the [[Zimbabwe Premier Soccer League]].\n\n=== FK Javor ===\n\nIn 2003 Temwanjera came to Serbia for trials with [[FK Javor Ivanjica]], a club that six months earlier had imported two of his CAPS United colleagues, [[Leonard Tsipa]] and [[Blessing Makunike]]. The season that he arrived, Javor had just been relegated from the top league, so Temwanjera played in the [[Serbian First League|Serbian Second League]] during his first two seasons. It was at the end of the 2004\u201305 season that Javor returned to the [[First League of Serbia and Montenegro]]. In the [[2005\u201306 First League of Serbia and Montenegro|2005\u201306]] season, Temwanjera played 26 matches and scored 3 goals. However, the club finished 12th and was relegated again.<ref>[http://www.srbijafudbal.net/javor.html Javor league positions of the last decade] at Srbijafudbal</ref>\n\n=== Borac \u010ca\u010dak ===\n\nIn the summer of 2006, the league in Serbia was renamed the [[Serbian SuperLiga|SuperLiga]]. FK Javor was playing in the [[Serbian First League]], formerly known as Second League. Temwanjera's performances in the previous season has caught the attention of some top league clubs, and in July he signed with [[FK Borac \u010ca\u010dak]]. By the end of the first half of the [[2006\u201307 Serbian SuperLiga]], Temwanjera had played 16 matches and scored 3 goals, and the club was having a mediocre season. During one march, discontented supporters shouted racially abusive remarks at Temwanjera, who decided to leave the club immediately afterwards.<ref>[http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport2/hi/football/africa/7287445.stm BBC report of another incident with mention to Temwanjera\u00b4s one]</ref> The quickest one to react was Romanian [[Liga I]] club [[SC Vaslui]] that brought him in that 2006\u201307 winter transfer window.\n\n=== Vaslui ===\nIn February 2007, Temwanjera completed his move to Vaslui on a four-and-a-half-year contract for an undisclosed fee.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.evenimentul.ro/articol/victima-a-rasismului.html|title=Victima a rasismului|date=5 February 2007|publisher=Vremea Noua|language=Romanian}}</ref> On 27 January, while he was still on trial, Temwanjera made his unofficial debut for Vaslui, against FCM B\u00e2rlad, scoring three times in the process.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.onlinesport.ro/stiri/fotbal/fotbal-intern/liga-1/fc-vaslui/13579/fc-vaslui-face-scor.htm?highlight=fc+vaslui|title=FC Vaslui face scor|date=27 January 2007|publisher=Onlinesport|language=Romanian}}</ref> On 24 February, Temwanjera made his competitive debut for Vaslui, in a 1\u20131 away draw against Farul Constan\u0163a.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.evenimentul.ro/articol/a-inghetat-farul.html|title=A inghetat Farul|date=26 February 2007|publisher=Evenimentul|language=Romanian}}</ref> Two weeks later, he scored the equaliser, in the 1\u20131 draw against FC Arge\u015f, counting his first Liga I goal.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.evenimentul.ro/articol/haisan-ingerul-pazitor.html|title=Haisan, ingerul pazitor|date=12 March 2007|publisher=Evenimentul|language=Romanian}}</ref> On 6 April, he scored twice in the home league match against Gloria Bistri\u0163a, once for his own team, and once in his own net. Vaslui eventually won the game with 3\u20132.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.evenimentul.ro/articol/un-meci-extrem-de-ciudat.html|title=Un meci extrem de ciudat|date=8 April 2007|publisher=Evenimentul|language=Romanian}}</ref> In the 2006\u201307 campaign, he played every single match for Vaslui, scoring three times and helping his team to finish 8th in Liga I, competition best at the time for the Moldavian team.<ref>{{Cite web|title=Clasament final|url=http://campionate.gsp.ro/competitii/fotbal/national/romania/liga-1/2006-2007/|publisher=Gazeta Sporturilor|accessdate=15 September 2011}}</ref>\n\nOn 27 July 2007, Temwanjera scored his team's second goal, in Vaslui's opening match against UTA Arad.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.sport365.ro/Liga_I__etapa_1__Vaslui___UTA_2_2-n29188.html|title=FC Vaslui 2\u20132 Uta|date=27 July 2007|publisher=Sport 365|language=Romanian}}</ref> Nine days later, he provided his first assist from the new season, helping Adrian Gheorghiu to score for 2\u20130, against Dinamo Bucure\u015fti.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.hotnews.ro/stiri-arhiva-1043713-soc-dinamo-vaslui-0-2-campioana-infatuarii.htm|title=SOC: Campioana infatuarii|date=5 August 2007|publisher=Hot News|language=Romanian}}</ref> On 31 October, Vaslui won against arch rivals Politehnica Ia\u015fi, thanks to Temwanjera's only goal from the 50th minute.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.mediafax.ro/sport/poli-iasi-fc-vaslui-scor-0-1-1020332|title=Poli Iasi 0\u20131 FC Vaslui|date=31 October 2007|publisher=Mediafax|language=Romanian}}</ref> Following a 0\u20131 loss against Steaua Bucure\u015fti, and due to his low goal-per-match rate, Temwanjera was put on the transfer list, alongside many other teammates.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.prosport.ro/fotbal-intern/liga-1/curatenie-la-fc-vaslui-2608665|title=Curatenie la FC Vaslui|date=4 May 2008|publisher=ProSport|language=Romanian}}</ref> However, on 7 May 2008, he wasn't for sale any more, following his two goals scored against Rapid Bucure\u015fti.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.romaniansoccer.ro/stiri/864/liga-i-ultima-etapa-fc-vaslui--rapid-2-4.htm|title=Vaslui 2\u20134 Rapid|date=7 May 2008|publisher=Romanian Soccer|language=Romanian}}</ref> He finished 7th with his team in Liga I, thus qualifying in the European Competitions, for the first time.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.onlinesport.ro/stiri/fotbal/fotbal-intern/liga-1/fc-vaslui/33276/caf-vasluiul-merge-in-intertoto.htm?highlight=fc+vaslui|title=CAF: Vaslui merge in Intertoto|date=19 May 2008|publisher=Onlinesport|language=Romanian}}{{dead link|date=January 2018 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref>\n\nAlthough in July 2008, it was rumoured that Metalurh Donetsk was interested in Temwanjera, he eventually remained in Vaslui.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.prosport.ro/fotbal-intern/liga-1/temwanjera-pleaca-la-donetk-2770667|title=Temwanjera pleaca la Donetsk|date=10 July 2008|publisher=ProSport|language=Romanian}}</ref> On 26 July, he scored his first European goal in UEFA Intertoto's Third Round, against Neftchi Baku, helping his team to advance in the UEFA Cup, for the first time.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.onlinesport.ro/stiri/fotbal/liga-europa/35922/fc-vaslui-in-cupa-uefa.htm?highlight=fc+vaslui|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120318084329/http://www.onlinesport.ro/stiri/fotbal/liga-europa/35922/fc-vaslui-in-cupa-uefa.htm?highlight=fc+vaslui|url-status=dead|archive-date=18 March 2012|title=FC Vaslui merge in Cupa Uefa|date=26 July 2008|publisher=Onlinesport|language=Romanian}}</ref> One week later, he scored the equaliser in the Moldavian Derby against Politehnica Ia\u015fi, match eventually won by Vaslui with 3\u20131.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.mediafax.ro/sport/poli-iasi-fc-vaslui-scor-1-3-2847248|title=Poli Iasi 1\u20133 FC Vaslui|date=2 August 2008|publisher=Mediafax|language=Romanian}}</ref> In August, he provided six points for his team, scoring Vaslui's winning goals against Gloria Bistri\u0163a<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.realitatea.net/liga-i-etapa-3-fc-vaslui-gloria-bistrita-1-0_329026.html|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110203091034/http://www.realitatea.net/liga-i-etapa-3-fc-vaslui-gloria-bistrita-1-0_329026.html|url-status=dead|archive-date=3 February 2011|title=FC Vaslui 1\u20130 Gloria Bistrita|date=8 August 2008|publisher=Realitatea|language=Romanian}}</ref> and O\u0163elul Gala\u0163i.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.romaniansoccer.ro/stiri/3842/liga-i-etapa-6--otelul-galati--fc-vaslui-0-1.htm|title=Otelul Galati 0\u20131 FC Vaslui|date=31 August 2008|publisher=Romanian Soccer|language=Romanian}}</ref> On 5 October, he scored his first cup goal, in his first Romanian Cup appearance against Politehnica Ia\u015fi.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.gsp.ro/fotbal/cupa-romaniei/final-fc-vaslui-poli-iasi-3-0-vaslui-se-califica-in-optimi-106671.html|title=Vasluiul se califica in optimi|date=4 October 2008|publisher=Gazeta Sporturilor|language=Romanian}}</ref> On 28 November, he scored his sixth league goal against Universitatea Craiova, surpassing his own personal tally from the previous season.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.antena3.ro/sport/fotbal-intern/sc-vaslui-u-craiova-1-1-punct-salvat-in-extremis-de-moldoveni-video-58979.html|title=Punct salvat in extremis de moldoveni|date=28 November 2008|publisher=Antena 3|language=Romanian}}</ref> On 18 April 2009, he scored Vaslui's third in a 4\u20133 home win against Politehnica Timi\u015foara.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://sport.hotnews.ro/stiri-fotbal-5609565-vaslui-timisoara-4-3-adevarat-spectacol.htm|title=Adevarat spectacol|date=18 April 2009|publisher=Hot News|language=Romanian}}</ref> On 6 May, he scored his last goal of the season, against Pandurii T\u00e2rgu Jiu, taking his tally of goals to 11.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.realitatea.net/final-fc-vaslui-pandurii-tg-jiu-1-0_512032.html|title=Vaslui 1\u20130 Pandurii|date=6 May 2009|publisher=Realitatea|language=Romanian}}</ref> Despite Vaslui's up and down season, he managed to finish 5th with his team, securing its spot for UEFA Europa League, for the second year in a row.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.onlinesport.ro/stiri/fotbal/fotbal-intern/liga-1/49873/fc-vaslui-pentru-al-doilea-an-in-europa-craiova-termina-sezonul-in-agonie.htm|title=FC Vaslui pentru al doilea an in Europa|date=10 June 2008|publisher=Onlinesport|language=Romanian}}{{dead link|date=January 2018 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref>\n\nTemwanjera started the 2009\u201310 season with a double in Vaslui's opening game against Omonia Nicosia.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://sport.hotnews.ro/stiri-fotbal-6011577-vaslui-omonia-nicosia-2-0-temwanjera-one-man-show.htm|title=Temwanjera \u2013 One Man Show|date=30 July 2009|publisher=Hot News|language=Romanian}}</ref> On 23 August, he scored his first league goal against Gloria Bistri\u0163a, giving his team a 2\u20131 lead. Vaslui eventually won with 3\u20131.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://backend.sport.ro/liga-1/19-00-gloria-bistrita-fc-vaslui-livetext-pe-www-sport-ro.html|title=Gata de Europa!|date=23 August 2009|publisher=Sport.ro|language=Romanian|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://archive.is/20120708070131/http://backend.sport.ro/liga-1/19-00-gloria-bistrita-fc-vaslui-livetext-pe-www-sport-ro.html|archivedate=8 July 2012|df=dmy-all}}</ref> On 23 September, he scored his second double from the season, in the cup match against Chimia Brazi.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.prosport.ro/fotbal-intern/cupa-romaniei/fc-vaslui-in-optimile-cupei-4926966|title=FC Vaslui in optimile Cupei|date=23 September 2009|publisher=ProSport|language=Romanian}}</ref> On 3 October, Temwanjera scored his team's second goal in Marius L\u0103c\u0103tu\u015f's first competitive match as manager, in Vaslui's 3\u20131 home win over Astra Ploie\u015fti.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.prosport.ro/fotbal-intern/liga-1/live-text-fc-vaslui-astra-3-1-pavlovic-inscrie-pentru-moldoveni-4957342|title=Lacatus a debutat cu dreptul|date=3 October 2009|publisher=ProSport|language=Romanian}}</ref> On 7 November, he scored the winning goal against Ceahl\u0103ul Piatra Neam\u0163.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://sport.hotnews.ro/stiri-fotbal-6429027-ceahlaul-piatra-neamt-vaslui-0-1-lacatus-neinvins-banca-vasluiului.htm|title=Lacatus neinvins pe banca Vasluiului|date=7 November 2009|publisher=Hot News|language=Romanian}}</ref> On 23 November, Temwanjera scored Vaslui's first goal, from the 2\u20130 home league win against CFR Cluj, helping his team winning the eighth match in a row.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://sport.hotnews.ro/stiri-fotbal-6549486-liga-1-vaslui-cfr-cluj-2-0-seria-incredibila-lui-lacatus.htm|title=Seria incredibila a lui Lacatus|date=23 November 2009|publisher=Hot News|language=Romanian}}</ref> On 27 February 2010, he suffered a meniscal laceration, in the 2\u20131 home league win against Pandurii T\u00e2rgu Jiu, which forced him out from the field for almost nine months.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.mediafax.ro/sport/fc-vaslui-pandurii-targu-jiu-scor-2-1-in-liga-i-5650233/|title=Vaslui 2\u20131 Pandurii|date=27 February 2010|publisher=Mediafax|language=Romanian}}</ref><ref name=\"mike\">{{cite news|url=http://www.vrn.ro/mike-a-inviat|title=Mike a inviat|date=13 April 2011|publisher=Vremea Noua|language=Romanian}}</ref>\n\nOn 4 November 2010, Mike was awarded \"Sportsman of the Year in Vaslui\", for his entire activity for the club.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.vrn.ro/mike-temwanjera-sportivul-anului-in-vaslui|title=Mike Temwanjera sportivul anului in Vaslui|date=6 November 2010|publisher=Vremea Noua|language=Romanian}}</ref> After being sidelined for nine months, he returned for Vaslui's 3\u20131 league win over Pandurii T\u00e2rgu Jiu on 26 November, coming as a late substitute for Yero Bello.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.prosport.ro/fotbal-intern/liga-1/eficienta-maxima-fc-vaslui-pandurii-3-1-7752900|title=Eficienta maxima|date=26 November 2010|publisher=ProSport|language=Romanian}}</ref> On 12 April 2011, he was in the startup team against Gloria Bistri\u0163a, for the first time since February 2010, and he managed to score Vaslui's only goal.<ref name=\"mike\"/> Late in April, following his Romanian citizenship request, he stated \"My future is tied with this town. I am happy here, and I want to end my career in the yellow-green shirt, when the time will come.\"<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.gsp.ro/fotbal/liga-1/mike-cel-mare-moldoveanul-din-zimbabwe-237113.html|title=Moldoveanul din Zimbabwe|date=21 April 2011|publisher=Gazeta Sporturilor|language=Romanian}}</ref> On 9 May, in a league game against Astra Ploie\u015fti, he was sent off for a bad foul on Alexandru M\u0103\u0163el.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.mediafax.ro/sport/astra-ploiesti-fc-vaslui-scor-1-1-in-liga-i-8253951|title=Astra Ploiesti 1\u20131 FC Vaslui|date=9 May 2011|publisher=Mediafax|language=Romanian}}</ref> He was punished with a two-match ban with two rounds to spare, meaning that Temwanjera's season was over.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.vrn.ro/final-de-sezon-pentru-mike|title=Final de sezon pentru Mike|date=9 May 2011|publisher=Vremea Noua|language=Romanian}}</ref>\n\nOn 24 July 2011, played his 100th Liga I match, in Vaslui's opening game against Rapid Bucure\u015fti.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.sport365.ro/Meciul_200_in_Liga_1_-n141561.html|title=Meciul 100 in Liga I pentru Temwanjera|date=24 July 2011|publisher=Sport365|language=Romanian}}</ref> He is only the second Vaslui player, to achieve this feat, joining Bogdan Buhu\u015f. On 18 August, Temwanjera scored his first goal of the season as he netted Vaslui's first in a 2\u20130 home win over Sparta Prague, helping his team qualifying for the first time in the UEFA Europa League's Group Stages.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.evz.ro/detalii/stiri/fc-vaslui-sparta-praga-2-0-moldovenii-au-detonat-bomba-942348.html|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110903110102/http://www.evz.ro/detalii/stiri/fc-vaslui-sparta-praga-2-0-moldovenii-au-detonat-bomba-942348.html|url-status=live|archive-date=3 September 2011|title=Moldovenii au detonat bomba|date=19 August 2011|publisher=Evenimentul Zilei|language=Romanian}}</ref> Three days later, he scored his first league goal of the season, in a 2\u20131 home defeat against newly promoted Ceahl\u0103ul Piatra Neam\u0163.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.prosport.ro/fotbal-intern/liga-1/i-au-ucis-in-10-minute-vaslui-ceahlaul-1-2-8634751|title=I-au \"ucis\" in 10-minute|date=21 August 2011|publisher=ProSport|language=Romanian}}</ref> One week later, he scored the 2\u20131 winning goal for Vaslui, against FC Bra\u015fov.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.vasluifc.ro/stiri-fcvaslui/886-fc-brasov-fc-vaslui-1-2.html|title=Brasov 1\u20132 Vaslui|date=28 August 2011|publisher=Vaslui FC|language=Romanian|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120331120649/http://www.vasluifc.ro/stiri-fcvaslui/886-fc-brasov-fc-vaslui-1-2.html|archivedate=31 March 2012|df=dmy-all}}</ref> On 11 September, he scored the equaliser against Dinamo Bucure\u015fti, counting his third league goal in a row. Vaslui went on winning with 3\u20131.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.gsp.ro/fotbal/liga-1/cronica-de-la-fc-vaslui-dinamo-3-1-victoria-gleznelor-fine-261598.html|title=Victoria gleznelor fine|date=11 September 2011|publisher=Gazeta Sporturilor|language=Romanian}}</ref> Four days later, he won a penalty that gave Vaslui a 2\u20131 lead in the first match from the group stages of [[UEFA Europa League]] against Lazio, after [[Wesley Lopes da Silva|Wesley]] converted from the spot. The game eventually ended a 2\u20132 draw.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.prosport.ro/fotbal-extern/europa-league/roma-orasul-minunilor-lazio-vaslui-2-2-wesley-a-reusit-o-dubla-8750989|title=Roma \u2013 Orasul minunilor|date=15 September 2011|publisher=ProSport|language=Romanian}}</ref> He scored his second goal in [[UEFA Europa League]] against [[FC Zurich]] in 2\u20132 draw. On 7 May 2012 he scored a hattrick against [[Gaz Metan Media\u015f]].He ended the season with a total of 7 goals in [[Liga I]].\n\n==International career==\nMike Temwanjera has made his debut for the [[Zimbabwe national football team|Zimbabwean national team]] in 2005 while playing with FK Javor in a friendly game against [[Zambia national football team|Zambia]]. That remained his only International appearance.<ref name=NFT>{{NFT player|id=30338}}</ref>\n\n==Personal life==\nHis brother [[David Temwanjera|David]] and [[Wilson Temwanjera|Jealous Wilson]], are also footballers too.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.herald.co.zw/on-fire-glamour-boys-face-struggling-blue-rangers/|title=On fire Glamour Boys face struggling Blue Rangers|work=The Herald|access-date=2018-05-23|language=en-GB}}</ref>\n\n== Statistics ==\n''Statistics accurate as of match played {{date|2014-05-19}}''<ref>{{RomanianSoccer|1979/mike-temwanjera.htm}}</ref><ref name=NFT/><ref name=SW>{{Soccerway|12132}}</ref><ref>{{WorldFootball.net|mike-temwanjera}}</ref>\n\n=== Club statistics ===\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align: center;\"\n|-\n!rowspan=\"2\"|Club\n!rowspan=\"2\"|Season\n!colspan=\"2\"|League\n!colspan=\"2\"|Cup\n!colspan=\"2\"|[[UEFA#Club|Europe]]\n!colspan=\"2\"|Total\n|-\n!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals\n|-\n|rowspan=\"9\"|[[SC Vaslui]]\n|[[FC Vaslui season 2006\u201307|2006\u201307]]\n|15||3||0||0||0||0||15||3\n|-\n|[[FC Vaslui season 2007\u201308|2007\u201308]]\n|26||5||0||0||0||0||26||5\n|-\n|[[FC Vaslui season 2008\u201309|2008\u201309]]\n|33||9||3||1||6||1||42||11\n|-\n|[[FC Vaslui season 2009\u201310|2009\u201310]]\n|18||5||3||2||4||2||25||9\n|-\n|[[SC Vaslui season 2010\u201311|2010\u201311]]\n|7||2||0||0||0||0||7||2\n|-\n|[[2011\u201312 FC Vaslui season|2011\u201312]]\n|30||7||3||0||7||2||40||9\n|-\n|[[2012\u201313 FC Vaslui season|2012\u201313]]\n|14||3||0||0||0||0||14||3\n|-\n|[[2013\u201314 FC Vaslui season|2013\u201314]]\n|31||5||2||2||0||0||33||7\n|-\n! Total\n!174!!39!!11!!5!!17!!5!!202!!49\n|}\n\n==Career honours==\n<ref name=SW/>\n;Vaslui\n*[[Liga I]] Runner-up: [[2011\u201312 Liga I|2011\u201312]]\n*[[Cupa Rom\u00e2niei]] Runner-up: [[2009\u201310 Cupa Rom\u00e2niei|2009\u201310]]\n*[[UEFA Intertoto Cup]] Winner: [[UEFA Intertoto Cup 2008|2008]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{NFT player|30338}}\n*{{RomanianSoccer|1979/mike-temwanjera.htm}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Tamwanjera, Mike}}\n[[Category:1972 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Sportspeople from Harare]]\n[[Category:Zimbabwean footballers]]\n[[Category:Zimbabwe international footballers]]\n[[Category:CAPS United players]]\n[[Category:FK Javor Ivanjica players]]\n[[Category:FK Borac \u010ca\u010dak players]]\n[[Category:FC Vaslui players]]\n[[Category:Bangkok United F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Serbian SuperLiga players]]\n[[Category:Liga I players]]\n[[Category:Thai League 1 players]]\n[[Category:Zimbabwean expatriate footballers]]\n[[Category:Expatriate footballers in Serbia]]\n[[Category:Expatriate footballers in Romania]]\n[[Category:Zimbabwean expatriate sportspeople in Romania]]\n[[Category:Association football forwards]]\n[[Category:Expatriate footballers in Thailand]]\n[[Category:Zimbabwean expatriate sportspeople in Thailand]]\n", "text_old": "{{EngvarB|date=May 2013}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=May 2013}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n| name      = Mike Temwanjera \n| image =\n| fullname = <!-- if different -->\n| birth_date = {{birth date and age|1982|5|21|df=y}}\n| birth_place = [[Harare]], Zimbabwe \n| height = {{Height|m=1.87|precision=0}} \n| currentclub =\n| clubnumber = \n| position = [[Forward (association football)|Striker]] \n| youthyears1 = | youthclubs1 = \n| years1 = 2001\u20132003 | clubs1 = [[CAPS United]] | caps1 = ? | goals1 = ? \n| years2 = 2003\u20132006 | clubs2 = [[FK Javor Ivanjica|Javor Ivanjica]] | caps2 = 26  | goals2 = 3\n| years3 = 2006\u20132007 | clubs3 = [[FK Borac \u010ca\u010dak|Borac \u010ca\u010dak]] | caps3 = 16 | goals3 = 3\n| years4 = 2007\u20132014 | clubs4 = [[SC Vaslui|Vaslui]] | caps4 = 174 | goals4 = 39\n| years5 = 2014\u20132015| clubs5 = [[Bangkok United F.C.|Bangkok United]] | caps5 = 14 | goals5 = 7\n| nationalyears1 = 2005 | nationalteam1 = [[Zimbabwe national football team|Zimbabwe]] | nationalcaps1 = 1 | nationalgoals1 = 0\n| pcupdate = {{date|2014-11-2}}\n}}\n\n'''Mike Temwanjera ''' (born 21 May 1982, [[Harare]]) is a former [[Zimbabwe]]an [[Association football|footballer]]. He usually played as a [[Forward (association football)#Centre forward|centre forward]], but also as a [[Forward (football)#Second striker|second striker]]. A member of [[FC Vaslui]] from January 2007 until summer 2014, he was one of the team's longest serving players, second in scoring during Vaslui's spell in Liga I, with 39 goals. He also appeared once for the [[Zimbabwe national football team|Zimbabwe national team]].\n\n== Club career ==\n\n=== CAPS United ===\n\nTemwanjera played until 2003 with [[CAPS United F.C.|CAPS United]], traditionally one of the strongest teams in the [[Zimbabwe Premier Soccer League]].\n\n=== FK Javor ===\n\nIn 2003 Temwanjera came to Serbia for trials with [[FK Javor Ivanjica]], a club that six months earlier had imported two of his CAPS United colleagues, [[Leonard Tsipa]] and [[Blessing Makunike]]. The season that he arrived, Javor had just been relegated from the top league, so Temwanjera played in the [[Serbian First League|Serbian Second League]] during his first two seasons. It was at the end of the 2004\u201305 season that Javor returned to the [[First League of Serbia and Montenegro]]. In the [[2005\u201306 First League of Serbia and Montenegro|2005\u201306]] season, Temwanjera played 26 matches and scored 3 goals. However, the club finished 12th and was relegated again.<ref>[http://www.srbijafudbal.net/javor.html Javor league positions of the last decade] at Srbijafudbal</ref>\n\n=== Borac \u010ca\u010dak ===\n\nIn the summer of 2006, the league in Serbia was renamed the [[Serbian SuperLiga|SuperLiga]]. FK Javor was playing in the [[Serbian First League]], formerly known as Second League. Temwanjera's performances in the previous season has caught the attention of some top league clubs, and in July he signed with [[FK Borac \u010ca\u010dak]]. By the end of the first half of the [[2006\u201307 Serbian SuperLiga]], Temwanjera had played 16 matches and scored 3 goals, and the club was having a mediocre season. During one march, discontented supporters shouted racially abusive remarks at Temwanjera, who decided to leave the club immediately afterwards.<ref>[http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport2/hi/football/africa/7287445.stm BBC report of another incident with mention to Temwanjera\u00b4s one]</ref> The quickest one to react was Romanian [[Liga I]] club [[SC Vaslui]] that brought him in that 2006\u201307 winter transfer window.\n\n=== Vaslui ===\nIn February 2007, Temwanjera completed his move to Vaslui on a four-and-a-half-year contract for an undisclosed fee.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.evenimentul.ro/articol/victima-a-rasismului.html|title=Victima a rasismului|date=5 February 2007|publisher=Vremea Noua|language=Romanian}}</ref> On 27 January, while he was still on trial, Temwanjera made his unofficial debut for Vaslui, against FCM B\u00e2rlad, scoring three times in the process.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.onlinesport.ro/stiri/fotbal/fotbal-intern/liga-1/fc-vaslui/13579/fc-vaslui-face-scor.htm?highlight=fc+vaslui|title=FC Vaslui face scor|date=27 January 2007|publisher=Onlinesport|language=Romanian}}</ref> On 24 February, Temwanjera made his competitive debut for Vaslui, in a 1\u20131 away draw against Farul Constan\u0163a.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.evenimentul.ro/articol/a-inghetat-farul.html|title=A inghetat Farul|date=26 February 2007|publisher=Evenimentul|language=Romanian}}</ref> Two weeks later, he scored the equaliser, in the 1\u20131 draw against FC Arge\u015f, counting his first Liga I goal.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.evenimentul.ro/articol/haisan-ingerul-pazitor.html|title=Haisan, ingerul pazitor|date=12 March 2007|publisher=Evenimentul|language=Romanian}}</ref> On 6 April, he scored twice in the home league match against Gloria Bistri\u0163a, once for his own team, and once in his own net. Vaslui eventually won the game with 3\u20132.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.evenimentul.ro/articol/un-meci-extrem-de-ciudat.html|title=Un meci extrem de ciudat|date=8 April 2007|publisher=Evenimentul|language=Romanian}}</ref> In the 2006\u201307 campaign, he played every single match for Vaslui, scoring three times and helping his team to finish 8th in Liga I, competition best at the time for the Moldavian team.<ref>{{Cite web|title=Clasament final|url=http://campionate.gsp.ro/competitii/fotbal/national/romania/liga-1/2006-2007/|publisher=Gazeta Sporturilor|accessdate=15 September 2011}}</ref>\n\nOn 27 July 2007, Temwanjera scored his team's second goal, in Vaslui's opening match against UTA Arad.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.sport365.ro/Liga_I__etapa_1__Vaslui___UTA_2_2-n29188.html|title=FC Vaslui 2\u20132 Uta|date=27 July 2007|publisher=Sport 365|language=Romanian}}</ref> Nine days later, he provided his first assist from the new season, helping Adrian Gheorghiu to score for 2\u20130, against Dinamo Bucure\u015fti.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.hotnews.ro/stiri-arhiva-1043713-soc-dinamo-vaslui-0-2-campioana-infatuarii.htm|title=SOC: Campioana infatuarii|date=5 August 2007|publisher=Hot News|language=Romanian}}</ref> On 31 October, Vaslui won against arch rivals Politehnica Ia\u015fi, thanks to Temwanjera's only goal from the 50th minute.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.mediafax.ro/sport/poli-iasi-fc-vaslui-scor-0-1-1020332|title=Poli Iasi 0\u20131 FC Vaslui|date=31 October 2007|publisher=Mediafax|language=Romanian}}</ref> Following a 0\u20131 loss against Steaua Bucure\u015fti, and due to his low goal-per-match rate, Temwanjera was put on the transfer list, alongside many other teammates.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.prosport.ro/fotbal-intern/liga-1/curatenie-la-fc-vaslui-2608665|title=Curatenie la FC Vaslui|date=4 May 2008|publisher=ProSport|language=Romanian}}</ref> However, on 7 May 2008, he wasn't for sale any more, following his two goals scored against Rapid Bucure\u015fti.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.romaniansoccer.ro/stiri/864/liga-i-ultima-etapa-fc-vaslui--rapid-2-4.htm|title=Vaslui 2\u20134 Rapid|date=7 May 2008|publisher=Romanian Soccer|language=Romanian}}</ref> He finished 7th with his team in Liga I, thus qualifying in the European Competitions, for the first time.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.onlinesport.ro/stiri/fotbal/fotbal-intern/liga-1/fc-vaslui/33276/caf-vasluiul-merge-in-intertoto.htm?highlight=fc+vaslui|title=CAF: Vaslui merge in Intertoto|date=19 May 2008|publisher=Onlinesport|language=Romanian}}{{dead link|date=January 2018 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref>\n\nAlthough in July 2008, it was rumoured that Metalurh Donetsk was interested in Temwanjera, he eventually remained in Vaslui.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.prosport.ro/fotbal-intern/liga-1/temwanjera-pleaca-la-donetk-2770667|title=Temwanjera pleaca la Donetsk|date=10 July 2008|publisher=ProSport|language=Romanian}}</ref> On 26 July, he scored his first European goal in UEFA Intertoto's Third Round, against Neftchi Baku, helping his team to advance in the UEFA Cup, for the first time.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.onlinesport.ro/stiri/fotbal/liga-europa/35922/fc-vaslui-in-cupa-uefa.htm?highlight=fc+vaslui|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120318084329/http://www.onlinesport.ro/stiri/fotbal/liga-europa/35922/fc-vaslui-in-cupa-uefa.htm?highlight=fc+vaslui|url-status=dead|archive-date=18 March 2012|title=FC Vaslui merge in Cupa Uefa|date=26 July 2008|publisher=Onlinesport|language=Romanian}}</ref> One week later, he scored the equaliser in the Moldavian Derby against Politehnica Ia\u015fi, match eventually won by Vaslui with 3\u20131.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.mediafax.ro/sport/poli-iasi-fc-vaslui-scor-1-3-2847248|title=Poli Iasi 1\u20133 FC Vaslui|date=2 August 2008|publisher=Mediafax|language=Romanian}}</ref> In August, he provided six points for his team, scoring Vaslui's winning goals against Gloria Bistri\u0163a<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.realitatea.net/liga-i-etapa-3-fc-vaslui-gloria-bistrita-1-0_329026.html|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110203091034/http://www.realitatea.net/liga-i-etapa-3-fc-vaslui-gloria-bistrita-1-0_329026.html|url-status=dead|archive-date=3 February 2011|title=FC Vaslui 1\u20130 Gloria Bistrita|date=8 August 2008|publisher=Realitatea|language=Romanian}}</ref> and O\u0163elul Gala\u0163i.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.romaniansoccer.ro/stiri/3842/liga-i-etapa-6--otelul-galati--fc-vaslui-0-1.htm|title=Otelul Galati 0\u20131 FC Vaslui|date=31 August 2008|publisher=Romanian Soccer|language=Romanian}}</ref> On 5 October, he scored his first cup goal, in his first Romanian Cup appearance against Politehnica Ia\u015fi.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.gsp.ro/fotbal/cupa-romaniei/final-fc-vaslui-poli-iasi-3-0-vaslui-se-califica-in-optimi-106671.html|title=Vasluiul se califica in optimi|date=4 October 2008|publisher=Gazeta Sporturilor|language=Romanian}}</ref> On 28 November, he scored his sixth league goal against Universitatea Craiova, surpassing his own personal tally from the previous season.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.antena3.ro/sport/fotbal-intern/sc-vaslui-u-craiova-1-1-punct-salvat-in-extremis-de-moldoveni-video-58979.html|title=Punct salvat in extremis de moldoveni|date=28 November 2008|publisher=Antena 3|language=Romanian}}</ref> On 18 April 2009, he scored Vaslui's third in a 4\u20133 home win against Politehnica Timi\u015foara.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://sport.hotnews.ro/stiri-fotbal-5609565-vaslui-timisoara-4-3-adevarat-spectacol.htm|title=Adevarat spectacol|date=18 April 2009|publisher=Hot News|language=Romanian}}</ref> On 6 May, he scored his last goal of the season, against Pandurii T\u00e2rgu Jiu, taking his tally of goals to 11.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.realitatea.net/final-fc-vaslui-pandurii-tg-jiu-1-0_512032.html|title=Vaslui 1\u20130 Pandurii|date=6 May 2009|publisher=Realitatea|language=Romanian}}</ref> Despite Vaslui's up and down season, he managed to finish 5th with his team, securing its spot for UEFA Europa League, for the second year in a row.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.onlinesport.ro/stiri/fotbal/fotbal-intern/liga-1/49873/fc-vaslui-pentru-al-doilea-an-in-europa-craiova-termina-sezonul-in-agonie.htm|title=FC Vaslui pentru al doilea an in Europa|date=10 June 2008|publisher=Onlinesport|language=Romanian}}{{dead link|date=January 2018 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref>\n\nTemwanjera started the 2009\u201310 season with a double in Vaslui's opening game against Omonia Nicosia.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://sport.hotnews.ro/stiri-fotbal-6011577-vaslui-omonia-nicosia-2-0-temwanjera-one-man-show.htm|title=Temwanjera \u2013 One Man Show|date=30 July 2009|publisher=Hot News|language=Romanian}}</ref> On 23 August, he scored his first league goal against Gloria Bistri\u0163a, giving his team a 2\u20131 lead. Vaslui eventually won with 3\u20131.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://backend.sport.ro/liga-1/19-00-gloria-bistrita-fc-vaslui-livetext-pe-www-sport-ro.html|title=Gata de Europa!|date=23 August 2009|publisher=Sport.ro|language=Romanian|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://archive.is/20120708070131/http://backend.sport.ro/liga-1/19-00-gloria-bistrita-fc-vaslui-livetext-pe-www-sport-ro.html|archivedate=8 July 2012|df=dmy-all}}</ref> On 23 September, he scored his second double from the season, in the cup match against Chimia Brazi.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.prosport.ro/fotbal-intern/cupa-romaniei/fc-vaslui-in-optimile-cupei-4926966|title=FC Vaslui in optimile Cupei|date=23 September 2009|publisher=ProSport|language=Romanian}}</ref> On 3 October, Temwanjera scored his team's second goal in Marius L\u0103c\u0103tu\u015f's first competitive match as manager, in Vaslui's 3\u20131 home win over Astra Ploie\u015fti.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.prosport.ro/fotbal-intern/liga-1/live-text-fc-vaslui-astra-3-1-pavlovic-inscrie-pentru-moldoveni-4957342|title=Lacatus a debutat cu dreptul|date=3 October 2009|publisher=ProSport|language=Romanian}}</ref> On 7 November, he scored the winning goal against Ceahl\u0103ul Piatra Neam\u0163.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://sport.hotnews.ro/stiri-fotbal-6429027-ceahlaul-piatra-neamt-vaslui-0-1-lacatus-neinvins-banca-vasluiului.htm|title=Lacatus neinvins pe banca Vasluiului|date=7 November 2009|publisher=Hot News|language=Romanian}}</ref> On 23 November, Temwanjera scored Vaslui's first goal, from the 2\u20130 home league win against CFR Cluj, helping his team winning the eighth match in a row.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://sport.hotnews.ro/stiri-fotbal-6549486-liga-1-vaslui-cfr-cluj-2-0-seria-incredibila-lui-lacatus.htm|title=Seria incredibila a lui Lacatus|date=23 November 2009|publisher=Hot News|language=Romanian}}</ref> On 27 February 2010, he suffered a meniscal laceration, in the 2\u20131 home league win against Pandurii T\u00e2rgu Jiu, which forced him out from the field for almost nine months.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.mediafax.ro/sport/fc-vaslui-pandurii-targu-jiu-scor-2-1-in-liga-i-5650233/|title=Vaslui 2\u20131 Pandurii|date=27 February 2010|publisher=Mediafax|language=Romanian}}</ref><ref name=\"mike\">{{cite news|url=http://www.vrn.ro/mike-a-inviat|title=Mike a inviat|date=13 April 2011|publisher=Vremea Noua|language=Romanian}}</ref>\n\nOn 4 November 2010, Mike was awarded \"Sportsman of the Year in Vaslui\", for his entire activity for the club.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.vrn.ro/mike-temwanjera-sportivul-anului-in-vaslui|title=Mike Temwanjera sportivul anului in Vaslui|date=6 November 2010|publisher=Vremea Noua|language=Romanian}}</ref> After being sidelined for nine months, he returned for Vaslui's 3\u20131 league win over Pandurii T\u00e2rgu Jiu on 26 November, coming as a late substitute for Yero Bello.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.prosport.ro/fotbal-intern/liga-1/eficienta-maxima-fc-vaslui-pandurii-3-1-7752900|title=Eficienta maxima|date=26 November 2010|publisher=ProSport|language=Romanian}}</ref> On 12 April 2011, he was in the startup team against Gloria Bistri\u0163a, for the first time since February 2010, and he managed to score Vaslui's only goal.<ref name=\"mike\"/> Late in April, following his Romanian citizenship request, he stated \"My future is tied with this town. I am happy here, and I want to end my career in the yellow-green shirt, when the time will come.\"<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.gsp.ro/fotbal/liga-1/mike-cel-mare-moldoveanul-din-zimbabwe-237113.html|title=Moldoveanul din Zimbabwe|date=21 April 2011|publisher=Gazeta Sporturilor|language=Romanian}}</ref> On 9 May, in a league game against Astra Ploie\u015fti, he was sent off for a bad foul on Alexandru M\u0103\u0163el.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.mediafax.ro/sport/astra-ploiesti-fc-vaslui-scor-1-1-in-liga-i-8253951|title=Astra Ploiesti 1\u20131 FC Vaslui|date=9 May 2011|publisher=Mediafax|language=Romanian}}</ref> He was punished with a two-match ban with two rounds to spare, meaning that Temwanjera's season was over.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.vrn.ro/final-de-sezon-pentru-mike|title=Final de sezon pentru Mike|date=9 May 2011|publisher=Vremea Noua|language=Romanian}}</ref>\n\nOn 24 July 2011, played his 100th Liga I match, in Vaslui's opening game against Rapid Bucure\u015fti.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.sport365.ro/Meciul_200_in_Liga_1_-n141561.html|title=Meciul 100 in Liga I pentru Temwanjera|date=24 July 2011|publisher=Sport365|language=Romanian}}</ref> He is only the second Vaslui player, to achieve this feat, joining Bogdan Buhu\u015f. On 18 August, Temwanjera scored his first goal of the season as he netted Vaslui's first in a 2\u20130 home win over Sparta Prague, helping his team qualifying for the first time in the UEFA Europa League's Group Stages.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.evz.ro/detalii/stiri/fc-vaslui-sparta-praga-2-0-moldovenii-au-detonat-bomba-942348.html|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110903110102/http://www.evz.ro/detalii/stiri/fc-vaslui-sparta-praga-2-0-moldovenii-au-detonat-bomba-942348.html|url-status=live|archive-date=3 September 2011|title=Moldovenii au detonat bomba|date=19 August 2011|publisher=Evenimentul Zilei|language=Romanian}}</ref> Three days later, he scored his first league goal of the season, in a 2\u20131 home defeat against newly promoted Ceahl\u0103ul Piatra Neam\u0163.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.prosport.ro/fotbal-intern/liga-1/i-au-ucis-in-10-minute-vaslui-ceahlaul-1-2-8634751|title=I-au \"ucis\" in 10-minute|date=21 August 2011|publisher=ProSport|language=Romanian}}</ref> One week later, he scored the 2\u20131 winning goal for Vaslui, against FC Bra\u015fov.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.vasluifc.ro/stiri-fcvaslui/886-fc-brasov-fc-vaslui-1-2.html|title=Brasov 1\u20132 Vaslui|date=28 August 2011|publisher=Vaslui FC|language=Romanian|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120331120649/http://www.vasluifc.ro/stiri-fcvaslui/886-fc-brasov-fc-vaslui-1-2.html|archivedate=31 March 2012|df=dmy-all}}</ref> On 11 September, he scored the equaliser against Dinamo Bucure\u015fti, counting his third league goal in a row. Vaslui went on winning with 3\u20131.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.gsp.ro/fotbal/liga-1/cronica-de-la-fc-vaslui-dinamo-3-1-victoria-gleznelor-fine-261598.html|title=Victoria gleznelor fine|date=11 September 2011|publisher=Gazeta Sporturilor|language=Romanian}}</ref> Four days later, he won a penalty that gave Vaslui a 2\u20131 lead in the first match from the group stages of [[UEFA Europa League]] against Lazio, after [[Wesley Lopes da Silva|Wesley]] converted from the spot. The game eventually ended a 2\u20132 draw.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.prosport.ro/fotbal-extern/europa-league/roma-orasul-minunilor-lazio-vaslui-2-2-wesley-a-reusit-o-dubla-8750989|title=Roma \u2013 Orasul minunilor|date=15 September 2011|publisher=ProSport|language=Romanian}}</ref> He scored his second goal in [[UEFA Europa League]] against [[FC Zurich]] in 2\u20132 draw. On 7 May 2012 he scored a hattrick against [[Gaz Metan Media\u015f]].He ended the season with a total of 7 goals in [[Liga I]].\n\n==International career==\nMike Temwanjera has made his debut for the [[Zimbabwe national football team|Zimbabwean national team]] in 2005 while playing with FK Javor in a friendly game against [[Zambia national football team|Zambia]]. That remained his only International appearance.<ref name=NFT>{{NFT player|id=30338}}</ref>\n\n==Personal life==\nHis brother [[David Temwanjera|David]] and [[Wilson Temwanjera|Jealous Wilson]], are also footballers too.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.herald.co.zw/on-fire-glamour-boys-face-struggling-blue-rangers/|title=On fire Glamour Boys face struggling Blue Rangers|work=The Herald|access-date=2018-05-23|language=en-GB}}</ref>\n\n== Statistics ==\n''Statistics accurate as of match played {{date|2014-05-19}}''<ref>{{RomanianSoccer|1979/mike-temwanjera.htm}}</ref><ref name=NFT/><ref name=SW>{{Soccerway|12132}}</ref><ref>{{WorldFootball.net|mike-temwanjera}}</ref>\n\n=== Club statistics ===\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align: center;\"\n|-\n!rowspan=\"2\"|Club\n!rowspan=\"2\"|Season\n!colspan=\"2\"|League\n!colspan=\"2\"|Cup\n!colspan=\"2\"|[[UEFA#Club|Europe]]\n!colspan=\"2\"|Total\n|-\n!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals\n|-\n|rowspan=\"9\"|[[SC Vaslui]]\n|[[FC Vaslui season 2006\u201307|2006\u201307]]\n|15||3||0||0||0||0||15||3\n|-\n|[[FC Vaslui season 2007\u201308|2007\u201308]]\n|26||5||0||0||0||0||26||5\n|-\n|[[FC Vaslui season 2008\u201309|2008\u201309]]\n|33||9||3||1||6||1||42||11\n|-\n|[[FC Vaslui season 2009\u201310|2009\u201310]]\n|18||5||3||2||4||2||25||9\n|-\n|[[SC Vaslui season 2010\u201311|2010\u201311]]\n|7||2||0||0||0||0||7||2\n|-\n|[[2011\u201312 FC Vaslui season|2011\u201312]]\n|30||7||3||0||7||2||40||9\n|-\n|[[2012\u201313 FC Vaslui season|2012\u201313]]\n|14||3||0||0||0||0||14||3\n|-\n|[[2013\u201314 FC Vaslui season|2013\u201314]]\n|31||5||2||2||0||0||33||7\n|-\n! Total\n!174!!39!!11!!5!!17!!5!!202!!49\n|}\n\n==Career honours==\n<ref name=SW/>\n;Vaslui\n*[[Liga I]] Runner-up: [[2011\u201312 Liga I|2011\u201312]]\n*[[Cupa Rom\u00e2niei]] Runner-up: [[2009\u201310 Cupa Rom\u00e2niei|2009\u201310]]\n*[[UEFA Intertoto Cup]] Winner: [[UEFA Intertoto Cup 2008|2008]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{NFT player|30338}}\n*{{RomanianSoccer|1979/mike-temwanjera.htm}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Tamwanjera, Mike}}\n[[Category:1972 births]]